Barcelona open their Champions League campaign against Borussia Dortmund this season. Both teams come into the clash after big wins in their respective leagues. Barca beat Valencia 5-2, while Dortmund hammered Bayer Leverkusen 4-0. The LaLiga champions have been struggling with injuries, but Lionel Messi is expected to play some part in the game. Kick off is 8pm West African time. Tuesday, September 17 Full time: It ends 0-0 between Dortmund and Barcelona. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.